The governorship candidate of the PDP in Ogun State, Hon. Oladipupo Adebutu, yesterday said the issues emanating from the conduct of the primary election in the state have been fully settled. Adebutu, who received the certificate of return from the party’s National Working Committee (NWC) on Tuesday, said his task is now to reconcile all aggrieved members of the party. He spoke with newsmen at the Murtala Muhammed Airport, Lagos shortly on his arrival from Abuja and was received by some chieftains of the party. Daily Trust reports that a factional candidate of the party, Mr. Segun Showunmi, had shortly after Adebutu was presented the certificate of return for the 2023 election, warned that the party may not have a governorship candidate in the election. However, Adebutu stated that Showunmi was merely expressing his opinion and he was entitled to it, noting that the party in Ogun State is now one big family and very resolute to ending “the misrule of the APC-led government. 